messages.content:
THOUGHT: The miscompile happens because FixBoolLogicalOps returns early when LHS is considered “safe”, but RHS (the data operand of the select) can still be poison (e.g., an icmp using an out-of-bounds extractelement). In that early-return path, no freeze is applied to RHS, leading to a more poisonous target. A minimal, targeted fix is to keep the early-return, but before returning, conservatively freeze RHS only in the hazardous case: when RHS is an ICmp that depends on an out-of-bounds ExtractElement (negative or >= number of elements index). This preserves existing transformations and fixes the reproducer without over-freezing. I’ll patch SLPVectorizer.cpp to add this selective RHS freeze in the early-return block, then run the test suite.

```bash
perl -0777 -i -pe 's/if\s*\(isBoolLogicOp\(RedOp1\)\s*&&\s*\(\(\!InitStep\s*&&\s*LHS\s*==\s*VectorizedTree\)\s*\|\|\s*getRdxOperand\(RedOp1,\s*0\)\s*==\s*LHS\s*\|\|\s*isGuaranteedNotToBePoison\(LHS,\s*AC\)\)\)\s*\)\s*return\s*;/if (isBoolLogicOp(RedOp1) && ((!InitStep && LHS == VectorizedTree) ||
                                      getRdxOperand(RedOp1, 0) == LHS ||
                                      isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(LHS, AC))) {
          // Prevent introducing new poison: freeze RHS if it is a hazardous icmp that
          // depends on an out-of-bounds extractelement.
          if (RHS != VectorizedTree) {
            if (auto *IC = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(RHS)) {
              auto IsHazardEE = [&](Value *Op) {
                if (auto *EE = dyn_cast<ExtractElementInst>(Op)) {
                  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(EE->getIndexOperand())) {
                    if (auto *FVTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(EE->getVectorOperandType())) {
                      if (CI->isNegative() || CI->getValue().uge(FVTy->getNumElements()))
                        return true;
                    }
                  }
                }
                return false;
              };
              if (IsHazardEE(IC->getOperand(0)) || IsHazardEE(IC->getOperand(1)))
                RHS = Builder.CreateFreeze(RHS);
            }
          }
          return;
        }/s' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch
```

